Brand Story By From the Manufacturer view largerNature Made Super B Complex Tablets, 140-countNature Made Super B-Complex supports cellular energy production. The formula provides a combination of all eight essential B vitamins (thiamin, riboflavin, niacin, pantothenic acid, vitamin B-6, biotin, folic acid, and vitamin B-12) and vitamin C that work together to help your body produce cellular energy from the foods you eat.†Helps Convert Food into Cellular Energy†The B vitamins are a family of eight unique vitamins that play several important individual and collective roles in your body. One of their key functions is to support the production of cellular energy from the foods you eat. When you consume a meal, all eight B vitamins are required for the metabolic processes that convert the carbohydrates, proteins and fats that you eat into cellular energy. This cellular energy is used to fuel your body’s many chemical reactions. Vitamin C is also required for cellular energy production from the fats that you eat.Nature Made Super B Complex combines all eight of the B vitamins plus vitamin C in one tablet, a convenient way to help maximize vitamins for cellular energy generation.†Supports Normal Function of the Nervous System†The B vitamins are also involved in biochemical reactions that support the normal function of your nervous system.† Essential for Proper Red Blood Cell Formation†B vitamins, particularly vitamin B-6, vitamin B-12, and folic acid, are required for the proper formation of red blood cells, which deliver oxygen to the body’s tissues.†Nature Made’s Commitment to Your HealthEveryone wants a firm foundation to stand upon when making decisions about their health. manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: HELPS SUPPORT BRAIN CELL & NERVOUS SYSTEM FUNCTION PLUS VITAMIN C+ This B complex supplement supports brain cell and nervous system function and includes Vitamin C, an antioxidant that helps support the immune system.+ SUPPORTS ENERGY METABOLISM(1)+ Nature Made Super B-Complex contains a combination of all 8 essential B vitamins (thiamin, riboflavin, niacin, B6, folic acid, biotin, pantothenic acid and B12), which help brain and body cells produce the energy they need to function. Vitamin B6 supports the production of neurotransmitters needed for mood health.+ (1)Helps convert food into cellular energy.+ 1 DAILY TABLET FOR ADULTS Adults, take 1 tablet daily with water and a meal. HIGH QUALITY INGREDIENTS Meets our high-quality standards. Made from carefully selected ingredients under strict manufacturing processes. No color added, no artificial flavors, gluten free.

UNDERSTANDING VITAMIN B B vitamins help brain and body cells produce the energy they need to function. These essential nutrients are vital for converting food into cellular energy and support nervous system function. There are 8 B vitamins generally included in the B complex: Thiamin (B1), Riboflavin (B2), Niacin (B3), Pantothenic Acid (B5), B6 (Pyridoxine), Biotin (B7), Folic Acid (B9), and B12 (Cyanocobalamin). Vitamins B6, B9 (Folic Acid) and B12 are often linked with brain health. They work together to help brain and body cells produce SAM-e, which is important for mood health.+ Adequate intake of B vitamins is especially important for those who experience low energy, eat plant-based diets, and women of childbearing age or pregnant women.+ B vitamins are foundational to whole body health, but various factors can influence how much of these essential nutrients we need and consume daily. For example, Folic Acid (B9) is particularly important for pregnant women and women of childbearing age. Vitamin B12 is important for vegetarians and vegans who may not consume enough from their diet alone. Dietary supplements can help provide essential B vitamins that may be lacking in the diet.+

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 27, 2012
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Glad I found this!
reviews.reviewText: I decided to start taking a B-complex vitamin after reading about the potential benefits of one - all of the symptoms that can be alleviated by it were symptoms I had, like moodiness, insomnia, low energy, mild depression-type symptoms, decreased concentration and memory, etc. I had chalked these up to having a toddler with irregular sleep patterns, but in retrospect I've had these symptoms for a long time and never could find what the underlying cause was, even with good sleep hygiene, good diet, exercise, etc.I noticed an IMMEDIATE difference in those when I started taking this supplement. I can definitely tell if I miss a dose. I take one tablet first thing in the morning, and I have tons of energy all day long and don't feel completely wiped out after work like I used to. I've never been a "morning person" and have always had a really long lag time before I feel like I'm totally awake...not any more! That's just amazing to me. I don't even really need my morning coffee in the morning! I'm quite pleased that it worked for me.I chose Nature Made as I have had good luck with their other supplements (folic acid, iron, vitamin C), in particular the iron supplement. It doesn't upset my stomach or cause an GI issues as is common with iron. B-complex supplements can cause nausea and stomach upset if taken on a empty stomach, but I have not had that experience with this supplement. IThe only negatives are that they smell a little strange (what vitamin doesn't, though?) and they turn your pee fluorescent yellow - but a) no one else sees your pee, and b) it happens because they are water soluble and the body excretes any excess that it doesn't need. It's impossible to get too much B-complex when taken orally because of that. The pills are small, so you don't have to choke down some giant horse pill every day. I also like the flip top cap on Nature Made products - so while the lids are NOT child-proof (so keep them out of reach of little ones!), they are convenient for something that is used every day. The caps are easy to open and close with a satisfying click.This size bottle will last a year, too - so great value for the price.
